# Vercel Dashboard Conventions

## Stack

Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Prisma ORM, Recharts, Neon Postgres.

## API Routes

All in `web/src/app/api/`. Pattern:

```typescript
import { prisma } from "@/lib/prisma";
const BOT_ID = process.env.BOT_ID || "richbot-pi";
export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  const data = await prisma.someModel.findMany({ where: { botId: BOT_ID } });
  return NextResponse.json(data);
}
```

- Always filter by `BOT_ID`
- Always set `dynamic = "force-dynamic"` (no caching for live data)
- Validate POST body types before writing

## Commands

POST `/api/commands` creates a pending command. The Pi polls and processes it.
Valid types: stop, resume, pause, status, performance, update_config.
Adding a new command: add to `validTypes` array in `route.ts` + add handler in `bot/multi_pair.py` `_register_cloud_commands()`.

## UI

- Dark theme: bg-surface (#0b0d17), cards bg-surface-card (#111827)
- Accent colors: green (#10b981), red (#ef4444), blue (#3b82f6), amber (#f59e0b)
- Font: Inter for text, JetBrains Mono for numbers/code
- Dashboard is single-page client component with 5s auto-refresh
- PnL positive = green, negative = red

## Prisma

- Schema: `web/prisma/schema.prisma`
- Column names are snake_case (@@map), model fields are camelCase
- After schema changes: `npx prisma db push` (dev) or `npx prisma migrate deploy` (prod)
- Raw SQL equivalent in `scripts/neon_schema.sql` — keep in sync with Prisma schema
